    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the complete plan to implement `Bun.INI`:\n\n---\n\n## Plan Summary: Add `Bun.INI` Public API\n\n**6 files to modify** (1 new, 5 edits), all following the exact patterns of `Bun.TOML`, `Bun.JSONC`, `Bun.JSON5`, and `Bun.YAML`:\n\n### Step 1 — CREATE `src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig`\nA self-contained Zig file with three public functions:\n- **`create()`** — builds a JS object with `parse` and `stringify` (mirrors JSON5Object.zig)\n- **`parse()`** — line-by-line INI parser: trims lines, skips `;`/`#` comments, maps `[section]` to nested JS objects, splits `key = value` at first `=`, throws `SyntaxError` on invalid input. Uses `callframe.arguments_old(1)` pattern from TOMLObject.zig.\n- **`stringify()`** — emits flat top-level keys first (`key = value\\n`), then object-valued keys as `[section]\\n` blocks. Uses `wtf.StringBuilder`. Imports at bottom per Bun Zig convention.\n\n### Step 2 — Edit `src/bun.js/api/api.zig`\nAdd `pub const INIObject = @import(\"./api/INIObject.zig\");` between `HashObject` and `JSONCObject`.\n\n### Step 3 — Edit `src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig` (4 additions)\n- **~line 69**: `pub const INI = toJSLazyPropertyCallback(Bun.getINIObject);`\n- **~line 137**: `@export(&BunObject.INI, .{ .name = lazyPropertyCallbackName(\"INI\") });`\n- **~line 1289**: `pub fn getINIObject(...) { return INIObject.create(globalThis); }`\n- **~line 2083**: `const INIObject = bun.api.INIObject;`\n\n### Step 4 — Edit `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h`\nAdd `macro(INI) \\` to `FOR_EACH_GETTER` alphabetically between `Glob` and `JSON5`.\n\n### Step 5 — Edit `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp`\nAdd one row to `@begin bunObjectTable` after the JSONC/JSON5 entries:\n```\n    INI    BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI    DontDelete|PropertyCallback\n```\n\n### Step 6 — Edit `packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts`\nAdd `namespace INI` block after `namespace TOML` (~line 794) with JSDoc for `parse(input: string): Record<string, any>` and `stringify(input: Record<string, any>): string`.",
